column12: Internal air and/or fuel staged controller
column13: A burner flame stabilizer which circumferentially stages the air to form circumferentially-spaced fuel rich and fuel lean zones for lowering of NO.sub.x is described. A circumferential solid fuel stager is described, which operates with a fuel stabilizer to provide increased dwell time for coal particles volatilization in a recirculation zone established by the flame stabilizer. Various embodiments are described.

column12: METHOD OF HEDGING RETAIL TRANSACTIONS FOR FUEL
column13: A method of executing a transaction related to the purchase of fuel. A contract is entered into by a purchaser with a card service provider or financial institution for a certain amount of fuel at a fixed or capped price offered over a predetermined duration. The fuel is purchased from a retail merchant. A payment is made or received by the purchaser depending on the difference between a prevailing retail index price and the fixed or capped price. A premium may be paid for entering into a capped price arrangement. The fixed and capped prices may be related to a retail index price at or before the time the contract is entered into. In another embodiment, the method includes receiving retail price index data for fuel sales and determining fuel sale contract criteria, with a fuel sale contract proposed for a purchaser.

column13: An apparatus 1 controlling the climate of an inner environment 3 comprises a heat exchanger 15 and a reversible heat pump 17 for controlling air temperature in the inner environment by heating (fig 1) or cooling (fig 2) air discharged into the inner environment. Air heated or cooled is dependent on the temperature of the air in the inner or an outer environment 5. A portion of the air from the outer environment may by-pass the heat exchanger and re-combine with the air flowing through the heat exchanger. Air quality in the inner environment may be controlled by replacing the air flowing from the inner environment to the outer environment. All air flowing to the inner environment may by-pass the heat exchanger if heating or cooling is not required (fig 3). The heat pump may heat or cool air that bypasses the heat exchanger, or heat or cool air re-circulated within the inner environment (fig 4). A humidifier 37 may control humidity of the air to the inner environment by adding steam or water to the air. One or more filters 31a, 31b, 33 may filter the air. Two fixed or variable speed fans 39, 41 supply or extract air.

column12: Video sensor with range measurement capability
column13: A video sensor device is provided which incorporates a rangefinder function. The device includes a single video camera and a fixed laser spaced a predetermined distance from the camera for, when activated, producing a laser beam. A diffractive optic element divides the beam so that multiple light spots are produced on a target object. A processor calculates the range to the object based on the known spacing and angles determined from the light spots on the video images produced by the camera.

column13: Patente de Invenção: <B>"MéTODO E APARELHO DE SOLDAGEM"<D>. Um aparelho e método para a soldagem de um artigo de superliga. O aparelho geralmente requer um recinto adaptado para conter um artigo de superliga, um aparelho soldador de arco transferido com plasma com reversão de polaridade para a soldagem de uma região localizada do artigo, uma bobina de indução para aquecer a região localizada, e dispositivo para sentir e controlar a temperatura da região localizada. A bobina de indução é colocada próxima à região localizada do artigo, de forma que a temperatura da região localizada é largamente determinada e rapidamente alterada pela saída da bobina. O aparelho para soldagem de arco transferido de plasma com reversão de polaridade é operado em correntes muito baixas de não mais do que quarenta e cinco amps, de forma que o aparelho para soldagem tem somente um efeito de aquecimento secundário comparado com a bobina de indução.

column13: An apparatus (10) and method for welding a superalloy article. The apparatus (10) generally entails an enclosure (12) adapted for containing a superalloy article, a polarity-reversing plasma transferred arc welder apparatus (20) for welding a localized region of the article, an induction coil (14) for heating the localized region, and means for sensing (24) and controlling (26) the temperature of the localized region. The induction coil (14) is placed in close proximity to the localized region of the article so that the temperature of the localized region is largely determined and quickly altered by the output of the coil (14). The welding apparatus (20) is operated at very low currents of not more than forty-five amps, so that the welding apparatus (20) has only a secondary heating effect compared to the induction coil (14).

column12: Kaynak çalismasi için bir isitma tertibati ve bunun için bir yöntem
column13: Bir süperalasim ürününün kaynaklanmasi için bir isitma tertibati ve yöntem. Tertibat ve yöntem, kaynak öncesi ve kaynak sonrasi isi islemlerinin, kaynaklama çalismasinin gerçeklestirildigi mahfaza ile ayni mahfaza içindeki bir ürün üzerinde gerçeklestirilmesini saglar. Tertibat, ürünün kaynaklanmasi için bir vasitayi, mahfaza içindeki ürünün isitilmasi için bir vasitayi ve ürünün sicakliginin algilanmasi için bir vasitayi kullanarak sicaklik islemi profilleri boyunca kaynaklanacak olan parçanin sicakligini dogru bir sekilde kontrol eder. Tertibat ayrica ürün için uygun kaynak öncesi ve kaynak sonrasi isi islemi sicaklik profillerini ve bir kaynaklama sicakligi profilini saklayan bir bellek depolama aygiti ile baglantili olarak da çalisir.

column12: HEATING DEVICE AND METHOD FOR WELDING OPERATION
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To realize efficient processing against superalloy articles which are produced, reversed, and restored by welding. SOLUTION: This invention provides a heating device 10 and a heating method for welding superalloy articles. According to the device 10 and the method, a heat treatment is applied to the articles before and after the welding in an enclosure 12 identical for performing a welding operation. The device 10 accurately controls the temperature of the articles to be welded during a total temperature treatment profile, using a means for welding the articles, a means 14 for heating the articles in the enclosure 12, and a means 24 for sensing the temperature of the articles. The device is also cooperated with a memory storage device for memorizing proper pre-welding and post-welding heat treatment temperature profiles and a welding temperature profile about the articles.
column15: BRODERICK THOMAS F;;WORTHING JR RICHARD ROY;;ROEDL LAWRENCE J;;POWERS JOHN M;;GROSSKLAUS JR WARREN D

column12: Heating apparatus for welding operation and method therefor
column13: A heating apparatus (10) and method for welding a superalloy article are described. The apparatus (10) and method provide for pre-welding and post-welding heat treatments to be performed on an article within the same enclosure (12) in which the welding operation is performed. The apparatus (10) accurately controls the temperature of the component to be welded throughout the temperature treatment profiles with the use of means for welding the article, means (14) for heating the article within the enclosure (12), and means (24) for sensing the article temperature. The apparatus (10) also works in conjunction with a memory storage device that stores appropriate pre-weld and post-weld heat treatment temperature profiles and a welding temperature profile for the article.

column12: Aparelho de aquecimento para operação de solda e seu respectivo método
column13: Patente de Invenção: <B>"APARELHO DE AQUECIMENTO PARA OPERAçãO DE SOLDA E SEU RESPECTIVO MéTODO"<D>. Aarelho de solda (10) e método para soldar artigo de superliga. O aparelho (10) e o método tornam possível realizar tratamentos térmicos pré-solda e pós-solda num artigo dentro do mesmo envoltório (12) no qual a operação de solda é executada. O aparelho (10) controla, com precisão, a temperatura do componente a ser soldado através dos perfis de tratamento da temperatura com o uso dos meios para soldar o artigo, meios (14) para aquecer o artigo dentro do envoltório (12) e meios (24) para detectar a temperatura do artigo. O aparelho (10) também trabalha em conjunto com um dispositivo de armazenamento de memória que armazena os perfis apropriados da temperatura de tratamento térmico pré- e pós-solda, e um perfil de temperatura de solda para o artigo.

column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To precisely control the temperature in an extremely local area of an article, generate a small controlled welding part, and improve physical and mechanical characteristics of the article to be a desired level. SOLUTION: This invention provides a device 10 and a method for welding a superalloy article. The device 10 is equipped with an enclosure 12 for accommodating the superalloy article, an inversion type plasma transfer arc welding device 20 for welding the local area of the article, an induction coil 14 for heating the local area, a means 24 for sensing the temperature in the local area, and a means 26 for controlling it. The induction coil 14 is arranged extremely near the local area of the article, whereby the temperature in the local area is mostly decided by the output of the induction coil 14 and changes rapidly. The welding device 20 is actuated at an extremely low current of 45 amperes or less, and so it has only a secondary heating function, compared with the induction coil 14.

column13: An apparatus and method for welding a superalloy article. The apparatus generally entails an enclosure adapted for containing a superalloy article, a polarity-reversing plasma transferred arc welder apparatus for welding a localized region of the article, an induction coil for heating the localized region, and elements for sensing and controlling the temperature of the localized region. The induction coil is placed in close proximity to the localized region of the article so that the temperature of the localized region is largely determined and quickly altered by the output of the coil. The polarity-reversing plasma transferred arc welding apparatus is operated at very low currents of not more than forty-five amps, so that the welding apparatus has only a secondary heating affect compared to the induction coil.

column12: Heating apparatus for welding operation and method therefor
column13: A heating apparatus (10) and method for welding a superalloy article are described. The apparatus (10) and method provide for pre-welding and post-welding heat treatments to be performed on an article within the same enclosure (12) in which the welding operation is performed. The apparatus (10) accurately controls the temperature of the component to be welded throughout the temperature treatment profiles with the use of means for welding the article, means (14) for heating the article within the enclosure (12), and means (24) for sensing the article temperature. The apparatus (10) also works in conjunction with a memory storage device that stores appropriate pre-weld and post-weld heat treatment temperature profiles and a welding temperature profile for the article.
column15: BRODERICK THOMAS FROATS;;WORTHING RICHARD ROY JR;;ROEDL LAWRENCE JOSEPH;;POWERS JOHN MATTHEW;;GROSSKLAUS WARREN DAVIS JR

column12: Kaynaklama yöntemi ve bunun için bir tertibat
column13: Bir süperalasim ürününün kaynaklanmasi için bir tertibat ve yöntem. Tertibat, genel olarak bir süperalasim ürününü içermek üzere uyarlanan bir mahfazayi, ürünün lokalize bir bölgesinin kaynaklanmasi için kutup degistiren plazma aktarimli bir kaynaklama tertibatini, lokalize bölgenin isitilmasi için bir endüksiyon bobinini ve lokalize bölgenin sicakliginin algilanmasi ve kontrol edilmesi için bir vasitayi içerir. Endüksiyon bobini, ürünün lokalize bölgesine yakin olarak yerlestirilir, böylece lokalize bölgenin sicakligi, büyük ölçüde saptanir ve bobin çikisiyla hizli bir sekilde degistirilir. Kaynaklama tertibati, yirmibes amperden büyük olmayan çok düsük akimlarda çalistirilir, dolayisiyla kaynaklama tertibati, endüksiyon bobinine kiyasla sadece ikincil bir isitma etkisine sahiptir.
column15: JR WARREN DAVIS GROSSKLAUS;;JR RICHARD ROY WORTHING;;ROEDL LAWRENCE JOSEPH;;POWERS JOHN MATTHEW;;BRODERICK THOMAS FROATS

column13: A relational database for migrating data in a workflow between databases in different environments. Graphical user interfaces are generated through which database management scripts are automatically generated for migrating data between environments. Generally, the database management scripts are compatible with database attributes. The database management scripts are executed to update data tables stored on the databases.

column12: Dual Step Bailout for Motorized RF Device
column13: Methods and devices are provided for retracting a cutting assembly in the event of a failure on a motorized electrosurgical device. A surgical device is provided that includes a handle portion with an elongate shaft extending distally therefrom. The elongate shaft has first and second jaws at a distal end, and the jaws are configured to engage tissue. The surgical device also has a cutting assembly configured to cut tissue engaged between the first and second jaws. A drive shaft extends from the handle of the surgical device through the elongate shaft and is coupled to the cutting assembly for moving the cutting assembly. The surgical device has a motorized gear assembly with at least one motor driven gear that is configured to move the drive shaft. The surgical device also has a bailout assembly that is configured to manually move the drive shaft.
